                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Subscription&#44; &#40;Postage Prepaid.&#41;<lb/>
                &#36;2.00 per annum &#45; &#45; for the U. S.<lb/>
                &#36;2.50 &#34; &#45; &#45; &#45; for Europe<lb/></p>
            <p>The MENORAH&#44;<lb/>
                A Monthly Magazine<lb/>
                of Hebrew Literature&#44; Science and Art.<lb/></p>
            <p>Benjamin F. Peixotto&#44; Editor.<lb/>
                39 Broadway&#44; Rooms 18 &#38; 19.<lb/>
                5647<lb/>
                New York&#44; Aug 16 1887<lb/></p>
            <p>My dear &#38; Rev friend&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>Thanks for your good letter and<lb/> promise.<lb/></p>
            <p>I beg now to enclose you<lb/> your poem sent me by D<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Felsenthal<lb/> and which he prayed I would first<lb/> submit to you before publishing<lb/> or requesting any one to translate<lb/> I had already handed it to our<lb/> mutual friend D<hi rend="sup">r</hi> H P. Mendes from<lb/> whom this morning I have a<lb/> reply enclosing Gruber&#39;s version<lb/> &#38; yours which appeared in the Heb<lb/> <hi rend="underline">Standard</hi> Oct 1&#47;86.  I do not quite<lb/> understand whether the Standard<lb/> published the <del>Hebrew</del> poem in Hebrew<lb/> with the English translation &#40;as given<lb/> by Dr. M&#41; and desirous of being<lb/> correct I send both to you to ask<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>of the Hebrew &#40;as given by D<hi rend="sup">r</hi> F&#41; is the<lb/> correct rendering &#38; if the translation<lb/> marked with green pencil is<lb/> satisfactory.  Also whether this<lb/> translation is D<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Mendes&#39;&#63;<lb/></p>
            <p>Please return D<hi rend="sup">r</hi> M&#39;s<lb/> letter in sending reply &#38; the poem<lb/> &#38; let me have all by return mail<lb/> if possible.<lb/></p>
            <p>I wish to give the Hebrew<lb/> with the English translation in<lb/> publishing same&#44; in the Menorah<lb/> for Sep<hi rend="sup">r</hi>.<lb/></p>
            <p>With sincere esteem<lb/>
                faithfully<lb/>
                Ben. F. Peixotto<lb/></p>
            <p>D<hi rend="sup">r</hi>. S. Morais<lb/>
                Phila.<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
